  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And so he and a little girl, [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Sasha, ?] she was very blond.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And she didn't remember who her parents were because she was given into a Polish family to survive, and her parents didn't survive.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And the-- the woman forgot-- the woman that she was by forgot her-- her-- her name she was born with, and till today, she still-- she would like to know, but she doesn't know who her-- her real name was before the war.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "She was hidden by a non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she was chosen-- a little beautiful, blonde little girl.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was the smallest, I think, one of the smallest from the six.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was Eva Lieber-- she is today Eva Lieberman, and she was-- she had a little sister.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were both brunettes, dark, and-- and that blonde little [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Sasha. ?] And there was another blonde girl.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was about my age.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she-- we six were chosen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- so here comes the adventure, out of Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were told that we're gonna-- a certain day, we're going to go on a train and we're going to go to the-- to the city of Warsaw, which was the capital once but it was completely demolished, 90%.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was bombed during the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when we came, there was nothing but rubble.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When we came to that city, I didn't realize it was so completely bombed that we walked on-- on bricks.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Demolished, like after the-- a war, you know, if ever saw a-- everything was bombed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was destroyed by-- both by the bombs and by the uprising.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So there was two things that demolished that city. 90% I was heard. 90% was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So only certain outskirts-- in the outskirts there were maybe some homes left.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
